meaning_str.bing:
n. 超市；超级市场
网络. 大超市；连锁超市；库存超市

大超市；连锁超市；库存超市

超市；超级市场；大型零售市场；自助商店；连锁超市

1.en: A few days ago I come across him in the supermarket.
1.cn: 前几天我去超市碰到他了

2.en: As it bulks up in financial services, that may give Britain's largest supermarket chain an edge over traditional insurers.
2.cn: 随着他们金融服务业务的膨胀，这给了英国最大的超市连锁店超越传统保险公司的优势。

3.en: A girl in care, Nina, is spotted by a French woman who believes her to be her baby, stolen years before from a supermarket trolley.
3.cn: 被收养所收容的女孩尼娜被一个法国女人所认出，她坚信尼娜就是她多年前在超市手推车里被人拐走的女儿。

0.en: Mummy Rabbit has arrived at the supermarket.

1.cn: 好了，超市到了！再见！乐器商店到了！再见！

2.en: Now imagine you live at the supermarket. Okay. No.
2.cn: 想像你住在超市里。好啊。不。

3.en: Can we go to the north pole? How about the supermarket? Yes, I don't think Teddy Playgroup has ever been shopping before.
3.cn: 所以我们可以去趟北极吗？呃，去趟超市怎么样？可以呀，我觉得小熊泰迪它以前肯定没有去过超市。

4.en: Remember how horrible it was when you guys bumped into each other at the supermarket? Oh God, yeah.
4.cn: 记得你们在超市巧遇的尴尬吗？没错。

5.en: These are frozen soya beans, also called edamame, from the supermarket, the raw ingredient of tofu.
5.cn: 这些都是在超市买的，速冻青豆，也叫毛豆，是做豆腐的原料。

6.en: Every time we go to the supermarket, though we might not know it, we're surrounded by corn.
6.cn: 每次我们走进超市的时候，或许我们意识不到，但我们被玉米包围了。

7.en: It is morning. Peppa is taking Teddy Playgroup to the supermarket. This shop sells everything.
7.cn: 现在是早上，佩奇带着小熊泰迪来到了超市。这个商店什么都有的。

8.en: What you seen in jungle, this is their supermarket, and whatever they can find, that's what they kill.
8.cn: 那一片丛林，就是他们的超市，他们能找到什么，就杀掉什么。

9.en: Can you remember, George? Dine-Saw! Dinosaur? George, there aren't any dinosaurs in the supermarket!
9.cn: 你能想起来吗，乔治？恐龙！恐龙？乔治，超市里根本没有恐龙！

10.en: OK, Rebecca, look after your auntie. Yes, Mummy. Mummy Rabbit has arrived at the supermarket.
10.cn: 好的，瑞贝卡，照顾好你的阿姨。好的，妈妈。兔妈妈首先来到了超市。

11.en: OK, Rebecca, look after your auntie. Yes, Mummy. Mummy Rabbit has arrived at the supermarket.
11.cn: 好的，瑞贝卡，照顾好你的阿姨。好的，妈妈。兔妈妈首先来到了超市。

12.en: Water. Water. Daddy Pig has reached the supermarket. All the running has made him very thirsty.
12.cn: 我要水，我要水。猪爸爸终于到达了超市。一路跑过来让他感到非常的口渴。

13.en: Then luckily, my Daddy lost him at the supermarket. But we found him again in the shopping.
13.cn: 不过幸运的是，我的爸爸在超市把它给弄丢了。但是我们又找到了它，就在购物袋里。

14.en: Then luckily, my Daddy lost him at the supermarket. But we found him again in the shopping.
14.cn: 不过幸运的是，我的爸爸在超市把它给弄丢了。但是我们又找到了它，就在购物袋里。

15.en: Here people they survive. They live to live, they don't live to get rich because here there is no supermarket.
15.cn: 这里的人为生存而活，他们自给自足，不求荣华富贵，这里你找不到超市。

16.en: Driving a bus is quite hard. Selling ice-cream is quite hard. Running a supermarket check-out is quite hard.
16.cn: 开公共汽车确实很难。卖冰淇淋确实很难。负责一个超市的收银台确实很难。

17.en: Driving a bus is quite hard. Selling ice-cream is quite hard. Running a supermarket check-Out is quite hard.
17.cn: 开公交车还是挺难的。卖冰淇淋也挺难的。在超市的收银台为大家结账也很难。

18.en: Driving a bus is quite hard. Selling ice-cream is quite hard. Running a supermarket check-out is quite hard.
18.cn: 开公交车还是挺难的。卖冰淇淋也挺难的。在超市的收银台为大家结账也很难。

19.en: George, there aren't any dinosaurs in the supermarket. No, George. The next thing on the Iist is onions.
19.cn: 我说乔治，超市里可没有什么恐龙你知道吗？不 乔治，清单上的下一种，是洋葱。
